        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Deuteronomy 3</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-13-2" n="13" prev="ADub.III.73.005.002.trl.xml#line-13-1" />
                        <l n="1">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            we turned and went up the way to Bashan. And Og, king of Bashan, came
                            out against us, he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and all his people, for war at Edrei.</l>
                        <l n="2">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            And the Lord said to me, “Do not be afraid of him, because I will give him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            and all his people and his land to your hand,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and you shall do to him as you did to Sihon, king of the Amorites,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            who dwelt at Heshbon.”</l>
                        <l n="3">So the Lord our God gave
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            to our hands Og, king of Bashan, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            all his people as well, and we struck him until he did not have a
                            remnant left.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="284r" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="4">And we took all his cities at that time.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            There was not a city which we did not take from them: sixty cities, all
                            the border
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            of Argob, the kingdom of Og in Bashan.</l>
                        <l n="5">All these cities were fortified
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            with high walls, gates, and bars — besides village-towns<ref
                                target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            a great many.</l>
                        <l n="6">And we desolated them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            as we did to Sihon, king of Heshbon, to put to destruction all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the men of the cities, women and infants.</l>
                        <l n="7">But all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            the livestock, and the spoil of the cities, we plundered for
                            ourselves.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="8">And we took at that time from the hand of the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            two kings of the Amorites the land that was at the ford of Jordan,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            from the river of Arnon to Mount Hermon,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="9">Sidonians call Hermon Sirion, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            the Amorites call it Senir,</l>
                        <l n="10">All the cities
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            of the plain and all Gilead and all Bashan as far as Salecah
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and as far as Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan.</l>
                        <l n="11">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            Because only Og, king of Bashan, remained of the remnant of the
                                <emph>Rephaim</emph>.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            Lo, his bedstead was a bedstead of iron, lo, in Rabbah,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            of the children of Ammon. Nine cubits was its length and four
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            cubits its breadth, after the cubit of a man.</l>
                        <l n="12">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            we inherited that land at that time.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            From Aroer which is by the river Arnon, and half
                            <milestone unit="page" n="284v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            the mountains of <addSpan spanTo="#add001" /><emph>Gilead</emph><anchor
                                xml:id="add001" /> and its cities: I gave it to the tribe of Reuben
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            and to the tribe of Gad.</l>
                        <l n="13">And the rest of Gilead, and all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            Bashan, the kingdom of Og, I gave to the half tribe of Manasseh.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            All the region of Argob, with all Bashan, was called the land of
                                <emph>Rephaim</emph>.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="14">Jair, son of Manasseh, took all the border of Argob
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            as far as the border of the Geshurites and the Maacathites and called them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the Bashan, after his own name, Havvoth-Jair, to this day.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="15">And I gave Gilead to Machir.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                        <l n="16">And I gave to the tribe of Reuben and to the tribe of Gad
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            from Gilead as far as the river Arnon the middle of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the river, and |it is| on the border, and as far as the place of the
                            river called Jabbok
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            was the border of the children of Ammon,</l>
                        <l n="17">and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            the steppe, and the Jordan, and |it is| on the border, from Kinnereth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            to the sea of the steppe, to the Salt Sea, under the riverbeds
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            <seg type="commented" n="#seg001" />of the summit<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn2"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> eastward.</l>
                        <l n="18">And I commanded
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            you at that time, saying, “The Lord your God has given you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            this land to inherit it. You shall pass armed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            in front of your brothers, all able men, the children of Israel.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="19">Only your wives and your infants and your livestock — I know that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            you have much livestock — shall abide in your cities which I have given
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            you.</l>
                        <l n="20">Until the Lord has given rest to your brothers,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="285r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            like to you, and they, too, inherit
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            the land which the Lord your God has given them at the ford of Jordan.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            And you will return every man to his inheritance which I have given
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            you.”</l>
                        <l n="21">And I commanded Joshua at that time, saying,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            “Your eyes have seen all that the Lord your God has done
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            to these two kings: so shall the Lord do to all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the kingdoms to which you are crossing.</l>
                        <l n="22">You shall not fear them,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            because the Lord your God: He is the one fighting for you.”
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            <emph>Parashat Vaʾetchanan</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="23">And I besought
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the Lord at that time, saying,</l>
                        <l n="24">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            “Oh Lord God, you have begun to show your servant your greatness,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            and your strong hand, because is there anyone so strong
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            in heaven or in earth that is able to do works like yours
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and braveries like yours?</l>
                        <l n="25">Now, let me cross
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and let me see the good land that is at the ford of Jordan, that
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            good mountain and Lebanon.”</l>
                        <l n="26">But
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            the Lord was angry with me because of you and he did not listen
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            to me. And the Lord said to me, “You have had enough. Do not go on speaking
                            <milestone unit="page" n="285v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            to me of this matter.</l>
                        <l n="27">Get up to the top
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            <seg type="commented" n="#seg002" />of the summit<anchor
                                type="commented" xml:id="seg002" /><ref target="#fn3"
                                type="noteAnchor" /> and lift up your eyes westward and northward
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            and southward and eastward and see it with your eyes: because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            you shall not go over this Jordan.</l>
                        <l n="28">And command
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            Joshua and reinforce him and strengthen him, because he
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            will cross before this people and will divide between them
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            the land which you shall see”.</l>
                        <l n="29">And we stayed
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            in <seg type="commented" n="#seg003" />the place called
                                <emph>Gay</emph><anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg003" /><ref
                                target="#fn4" type="noteAnchor" /> opposite Beth-Peor.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
